1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,200
Why didn't you tell me
you're carrying my baby?

2
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,480
The baby in Pin's womb is mine.

3
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,440
<i>Let's get the divorce.</i>

4
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:33,240
Even if you're not pregnant,
I was divorcing you anyway.

5
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,200
I won't waste my time on someone like you.

6
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,480
See for yourself, Aunt Un.

7
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:41,960
Your blind love and gratitude
are destroying everyone's lives,

8
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,560
including your own daughter's.

9
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:46,240
Mr. Tong, I need your help.

10
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,240
If you don't leave,
I won't hesitate to shoot you.

11
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,720
Yai kidnapped Aunt Un.

12
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,880
He broke the law,
and you're still siding with him?

13
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,280
What about you? You knew Pin was married,

14
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,000
so why did you still do something wrong?

15
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,520
Why didn't you think about it?

16
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,880
Yai took Pin away from me.

17
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,880
I just took my girl back.

18
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,840
Jom.

19
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,280
Mr. Yai probably didn't take Mom.

20
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,520
Let's go find her.

21
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,040
Pin! Wait! Pin!

22
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,640
Mr. Yai.

23
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,160
I'm sorry for that brat of a son.

24
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:46,040
It's okay. I'm more worried
about Aunt Un now.

25
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,320
Un was cruel enough to poison you.

26
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,840
Why do you still worry about her?

27
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:54,200
She's a key witness for us
to be able to put Krongsuk in prison.

28
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,840
Where have you been?

29
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,360
Why haven't you come home?

30
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,280
I'm afraid of that perverted den boss.

31
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:09,240
So disgusting. I wanna throw up.

32
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,480
He won't mess with you anymore.

33
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,560
No need to be afraid.

34
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:15,920
No, I won't risk it.

35
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,760
Auntie, transfer me some money.

36
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,959
I'll go live on my own.

37
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,000
Madam.

38
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:26,240
If you don't come back,
don't expect to get a single baht from me.

39
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,080
How's Un doing?

40
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,520
Not very good.

41
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,560
When she woke up, she asked only for you.

42
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,280
Madam?

43
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,160
How did you get here? Did Yai see you?

44
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:30,000
No. But I heard that you're sick,

45
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,160
so I rushed here because I was worried.

46
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,880
And I overheard Yai talking
to his subordinates

47
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:39,560
that he plans to take you hostage
to lure Pin out,

48
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:42,400
so he could kill both of you for revenge.

49
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,920
Hey, why did you come out?

50
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,200
Get back inside.

51
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:50,240
What's that? Are you all drug dealers?

52
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,760
You're starting to know too much.

53
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,800
No, Mr. Tong.

54
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,480
She's still useful to us.

55
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:06,160
Of course, my dear wife.

56
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:12,000
How could you become
a wife of a man like him, Madam?

57
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:15,080
How could you live with him,
knowing he's a drug dealer?

58
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,800
Because he can help me kill Yai

59
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:20,000
and get rid of all my enemies.

60
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,280
So…

61
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,320
you are

62
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:32,320
the one who ran over Pha
and killed him, right?

63
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,760
Yai told you, didn't he?

64
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,240
Yes.

65
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,800
Because that criminal was too ambitious.

66
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:44,520
I started a new life at Paisal Farm,

67
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,680
but he still followed,
trying to blackmail me.

68
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:50,560
Unfortunately, Yai happened to see us.

69
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,520
<i>If Pha had died right then,</i>

70
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:59,760
<i>I wouldn't have needed</i>
<i>to put in the effort to kill him myself.</i>

71
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:06,200
But Pha was your husband,
and the father of…

72
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:08,200
He couldn't be anyone's father!

73
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:13,240
If he hadn't squandered all the money
Dad left me until we were broke,

74
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:16,440
I wouldn't have had to agree
to become that old man Paisal's wife.

75
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:23,040
So, Mr. Paisal fell ill and died

76
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,640
because you poisoned him?

77
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,800
That's the least torturous way

78
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:33,039
for a benefactor, isn't it?

79
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,920
Un.

80
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,560
You need to understand

81
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,320
that I did everything to survive.

82
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,360
For Na and for Nee.

83
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:18,240
But it's a sin, Madam. Please stop.

84
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,880
Let Mr. Yai go.

85
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:24,000
And I'll stay to serve you

86
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:28,960
and earn money to take care of you,
Mr. Na, and Ms. Nee myself. Please.

87
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,600
Un. Someone like you?

88
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,920
You must be watching
too many local dramas.

89
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:43,120
But I can't stand to see you
continue doing something wrong.

90
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,560
So can you stand to see me go to jail?!

91
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,920
Madam…

92
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,200
In the end,

93
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,840
no one really loved me,

94
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,560
not even you.

95
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,160
‪Pin…

96
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,520
I'm sorry…

97
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:52,080
I'm sorry I never believed you.

98
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,960
I'm sorry…

99
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,560
What are you gonna do with her?

100
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,920
I'll use her to lure Yai out
so you can kill him.

101
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,760
What about the share?

102
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,720
A fifty-fifty split of the inheritance.

103
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,160
Is that enough?

104
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,880
This is what they call true love.

105
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:42,920
Pin?

106
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,920
Did you know where Aunt Un is?

107
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,640
I'm going to file a police report.

108
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,600
But…

109
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:51,360
It's time to face the truth.

110
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,880
I just want Mom to be safe.

111
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,280
I'll drive.

112
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:56,520
Let's go.

113
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,520
Yai.

114
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,520
What did the hospital say?

115
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:07,200
There was no security camera
right outside the room.

116
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,240
We can only see the ward entrance.

117
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:20,680
But someone else showed up at the ward
before Aunt Un disappeared.

118
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,480
Someone unexpected.

119
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,360
That witch.

120
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:31,120
I can even recognize her shadow.

121
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:35,000
But there's no footage of them going out
together. We can't use this as evidence.

122
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,600
Hello. Who's this?

123
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,480
How are you doing, Mr. Yai?

124
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:58,320
Madam Krongsuk. Where's Aunt Un?

125
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,000
How should I know?

126
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,120
By the time I got to the hospital,
she was no longer there.

127
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,640
Why don't you ask the hospital staff?

128
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,960
I'm calling you
because I'm worried about her.

129
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:14,200
<i>So I want to invite you here</i>
<i>to talk this out.</i>

130
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,640
Dad.

131
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,000
Can't you see what he's doing?

132
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:42,440
Dad, Madam Krongsuk called
to get Mr. Yai to negotiate with her.

133
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:45,240
Mr. Yai believes that Aunt Un's with her.

134
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:49,200
Pan, gather as many
of our men as possible. Now.

135
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:50,520
Yes, Dad.

136
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:02,400
Mr. Yai, pick up.

137
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,120
Just pick up.

138
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,280
What do I do?

139
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:25,320
Hey. You hired me
and my truck for two days,

140
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,200
but I've only seen half the cash.

141
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:30,320
I'm going to get the money
for you right now.

142
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,400
Or what?

143
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,560
Are you going to take me to the police?

144
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,920
If I go to jail, you won't get paid.

145
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,880
What do you want?

146
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,640
Alright, alright.

147
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,120
Where do you want to go next?

148
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,280
Madam, she's gone!

149
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,640
Go look for her now.

150
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,200
Madam…

151
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:47,560
Madam… Madam…

152
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:50,800
Please.

153
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:56,640
I helped your father take care of you
and have served you all this time.

154
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:01,440
I love you with all my heart

155
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,320
and my whole life.

156
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:09,000
I don't want to see you
kill anyone anymore.

157
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,720
You're all the same.

158
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,240
Paisal told me the same thing,

159
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,000
but he left me nothing in his will.

160
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,560
Same with Pha.

161
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,720
I once thought I could rely on him,

162
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:30,240
but then he drained every baht I had.

163
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:32,960
They both deserved to die.

164
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,800
And so do you.

165
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,160
Madam…

166
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,080
Have you ever loved me?

167
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:54,880
Or do you only see me as your lapdog?

168
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,840
Of course, I love you.

169
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,800
Why wouldn't I love my loyal lapdog?

170
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,520
I'm really sorry, Un.

171
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,440
Hello.

172
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,720
I'm here.

173
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,800
If you want to negotiate, just come out.

174
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:29,240
Aunt Un? Aunt Un.

175
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:32,560
Aunt Un.

176
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:35,520
Aunt Un.

177
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,800
I thought you said
you'd be waiting at the warehouse

178
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,360
to hear that my men
had successfully gotten rid of Yai.

179
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:55,320
And what is this? Whose blood is that?

180
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,920
It's Un's blood.

181
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,480
I planned to use her
as bait to lure Yai out,

182
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:04,640
but she turned on me
and tried to run to the police,

183
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,720
so I had to kill her.

184
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:17,400
Hey, all of you, go get Yai right now.

185
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:20,680
Tie them both up and burn them,
both Yai and Un. Go.

186
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:24,480
Let's go.

187
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:32,840
I'm sorry.

188
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:37,640
Who did this to you?

189
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:41,960
Mr. Paisal…

190
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:49,520
Mr. Paisal was poisoned. The one…

191
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:53,000
who did it is…

192
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,880
Ma…

193
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,360
Aunt Un.

194
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,280
Aunt Un.

195
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,440
Aunt Un.

196
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:09,880
Aunt Un. You can't die like this.

197
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:14,840
Take care of Pin for me…

198
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:22,840
Aunt Un.

199
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,320
This is a life and death situation.

200
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,120
Why do you need a stupid search warrant?

201
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,280
Paisal Farm is private property.

202
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:43,200
We are police officers.
We need to operate within the law.

203
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:45,600
Right now, you just suspect that

204
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:48,200
the patient was abducted,
but there's still no evidence for that.

205
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:51,600
But the nurse confirmed that
Mr. Yai went into Aunt Un's room.

206
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,840
Do you need to wait
for someone to get killed first?

207
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,600
Then just about anyone could be a cop.

208
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:56,560
Jom.

209
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,880
Let's go look by ourselves for now.

210
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,120
Ms. Nee?

211
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,120
Pin, come help your mom right now.

212
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,800
I just sent you the location.

213
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:26,200
I don't know anything.

214
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:28,000
I don't care if you believe me or not.

215
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,280
PROFESSIONAL POLICE FORCE
FOR PUBLIC WELL-BEING

216
00:22:30,360 --> 00:22:33,440
I called for reinforcements
near the scene to rush over.

217
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:35,080
We're mobilizing there.

218
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,680
POLICE STATION

219
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:42,520
Aunt Un. You can't die like this, Aunt Un.

220
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,360
Aunt Un! Aunt Un.

221
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:08,800
Hey.

222
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,960
Who sent you?

223
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:43,400
Put the gun down.

224
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,000
I said put the gun down.

225
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,680
Lay down cover fire to stop the police.

226
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,280
Don't let them follow Mr. Yai.

227
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:09,960
Go!

228
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:24,120
Hey, split up and run.

229
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,880
I'll follow Mr. Yai.

230
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,040
Go.

231
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,600
Freeze!

232
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:06,440
He's with Yai.

233
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,120
Uncle Pload?

234
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:09,560
Pin.

235
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:15,880
Someone has been
stabbed to death over here.

236
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,960
- Pin.
- Pin.

237
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,200
- Pin.
- Pin!

238
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,960
- Go, go!
- Come on!

239
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:41,480
‪062-6639826 FARM

240
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:33,640
Hey, go look.

241
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,600
It's done, Boss.

242
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,560
So I'm living alone in this house?

243
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:58,640
I'm living alone.

244
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,760
That means if I slack off,

245
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,320
no one would know.

246
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:07,160
Oh, Noi. You've been so stupid.

247
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:12,080
Let Madam Noi take a nap for once.

248
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,120
So soft.

249
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,400
Awesome.

250
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:21,560
Noi.

251
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,720
I'm not even asleep yet.

252
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:24,880
How could I be having a nightmare?

253
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,800
You want to fall asleep forever?!

254
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:34,280
Madam?! Madam. I'm sorry.

255
00:28:34,360 --> 00:28:36,160
How did you get here?

256
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:38,360
Where are Pan and Pload?

257
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:44,080
Let go of me.

258
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:45,480
Can you just shut up?

259
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,560
Hey.

260
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:51,920
Go! Get down there!

261
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,520
- Let go!
- Careful.

262
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,000
- Let go of me!
- Come here.

263
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,200
Get down!

264
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:57,880
Come here.

265
00:28:58,800 --> 00:28:59,960
- Hey!
- Hey.

266
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:00,880
Beat him up.

267
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:03,000
No, no! Don't!

268
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:06,160
No! Don't do it! Don't hurt him.

269
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:08,120
Can't we just talk?

270
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,800
All of you, remember this.

271
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,560
If the police ask about Yai,

272
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:15,800
tell them he's a criminal
who has been trying to rob the farm

273
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:18,800
and who planned to kill Madam,
so she had to run away.

274
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:22,680
Keep running your mouths
and see what happens.

275
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,880
We've looked everywhere.
There's no one here.

276
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:36,080
You didn't lie to me, did you, Noi?

277
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:40,000
I swear, I don't know.

278
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:48,080
Go prepare a room for Mr. Tong.

279
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,720
Just use Yai's room.

280
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:52,000
Burn all of his belongings.

281
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:56,480
What if Mr. Yai comes back
and breaks my neck?

282
00:29:57,880 --> 00:30:00,120
He can't break anyone's neck now.

283
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:07,000
Are you going to prepare the room,
or are you going to pack up and leave?

284
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,000
Alright, Madam.

285
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:15,640
I rounded up all the farm workers,

286
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:18,760
but the supervisor
and Pload's son are still missing.

287
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:21,800
They know our secrets.

288
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,400
We can't let them live.

289
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,200
Go hunt them down.

290
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,360
Kill them on the spot.

291
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:34,960
Send them all
to the same hell Yai just went to.

292
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,040
Yes, Boss.

293
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,560
Mom.

294
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,400
Did you feel a lot of pain?

295
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,560
I'm sorry, Mom…

296
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:56,560
I'm sorry
I couldn't take care of you better.

297
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,440
I've failed as a daughter.

298
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:07,080
I'm a terrible daughter.

299
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:14,000
You must be so upset with me.

300
00:31:16,120 --> 00:31:18,320
Is that why you won't talk to me?

301
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:30,800
Pin.

302
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:34,360
Aunt Un's in a better place now.

303
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:38,320
She's no longer in pain.

304
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:46,280
You need to stay strong, Pin.

305
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:50,320
She wouldn't want to see you like this.

306
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:52,520
I'll kill Yai

307
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,920
and wash Aunt Un's feet with his blood.

308
00:31:58,080 --> 00:31:59,440
What the hell are you saying?

309
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:01,800
Our country has laws.

310
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:04,040
How could you just kill someone like that?

311
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:05,680
Also,

312
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:08,880
the police still haven't
even concluded that Mr. Yai did it.

313
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:12,360
But the police confirmed that
he was the last person seen with Aunt Un.

314
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,560
His hands were covered in blood too.

315
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:20,600
And if he didn't do anything wrong,
why would he run from the police?

316
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:24,560
Someone like him has to pay with his life.

317
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,560
Enough.

318
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:27,920
Stop it.

319
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:31,000
I don't want to hear any more of that.

320
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:33,440
Pin?

321
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:39,640
Jom. Jom!

322
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:54,080
I'm right here, Mom.

323
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:01,240
I won't let you go anywhere.

324
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:04,760
And I won't leave you either.

325
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:58,400
Pin, what's wrong?

326
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,960
You keep hurting yourself.

327
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:05,160
The closet is
full of new clothes I bought you.

328
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,800
Why waste time mending it?

329
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,840
I'm just fixing this button
on your shirt for you.

330
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:15,480
I looked everywhere for a matching button
but ended up buying it online.

331
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,280
Next time, you don't have to.

332
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,600
It's not a big deal.

333
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:31,120
No, I just want to make your heart throb.

334
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:38,480
I'm just showing a bit of my chest.

335
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:40,080
Come here.

336
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,320
- Come on.
- Mr. Yai.

337
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,360
Hey, wait.

338
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:45,480
- Back off right now.
- Are you seriously going to poke my eye?

339
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:47,159
- Fine. Come on, Pin.
- I'll poke you.

340
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:48,400
Come here.

341
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,639
Excuse me.

342
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:00,760
The autopsy results are out.

343
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:04,320
Your mother's death
was caused by multiple stab wounds.

344
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:11,760
Currently, your husband, Mr. Chalit,
is the prime suspect.

345
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,600
May I ask if he had
any conflict with the deceased?

346
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:24,280
We… We separated for a while already.

347
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,600
And we haven't been in contact.

348
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:34,160
Did you apprehend him, Officer?

349
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,640
Not yet.

350
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:38,320
But his motorcycle was found
at the bottom of a ravine.

351
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,080
Pin.

352
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,320
Is he dead, Mr. Tong?

353
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,280
Haven't found him.

354
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:10,240
Rescuers are combing the area to find him.

355
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:14,840
It's a deep ravine,
so it might take some time.

356
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:19,800
But I don't think he would have survived.

357
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:32,400
Finally, this farm is mine.

358
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:38,600
Did you forget about my half?

359
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:44,240
No, I didn't.

360
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:48,640
But we have to wait just a little longer
for the court proceedings to conclude.

361
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:49,800
How about this?

362
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,920
I'll ask Na to talk with the lawyer

363
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:55,360
to find a way to get you
the first part of the inheritance.

364
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,560
Is that good?

365
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:02,480
That's what they call true love.

366
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:06,120
But wait. Our job isn't done.

367
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,120
There's still Pload.

368
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,840
Pload of Padang Besar?

369
00:37:14,120 --> 00:37:16,840
The brave tiger has now become a dog.

370
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:40,920
Mr. Pload.

371
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:43,120
Are you ready to give a statement?

372
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:50,080
I've already given one.

373
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:56,240
Everything that happened
was due to Madam Krongsuk's plan.

374
00:37:57,240 --> 00:38:01,200
There's no way
Mr. Yai killed Pinanong's mother.

375
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,760
But we still haven't found
Mr. Chalit's body.

376
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:07,080
So you should confess everything now,

377
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:08,440
for everyone's sake.

378
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:11,760
Body? Whose body?

379
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:45,000
<i>Should I believe what my mind tells me</i>

380
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:48,040
<i>or the evidence in my hand, Mom?</i>

381
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,000
Just tell me, Jin.

382
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,240
The police only found
the wreckage of a motorcycle,

383
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:20,880
and Jom recognized that
it was the one Mr. Yai used to ride.

384
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:24,240
But…

385
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,720
they couldn't find Mr. Yai's body

386
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,920
because the flash floods down there
have very strong currents.

387
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:37,960
The body has likely been swept far away.

388
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:44,040
Pin, Pin.

389
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,400
He killed Aunt Un.

390
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:52,120
Why do you have to mourn that monster?

391
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,200
It's only fitting that he dies.

392
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:58,440
I only regret
that I didn't kill him myself.

393
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:04,360
- Pin? Pin.
- Don't follow her.

394
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:08,200
Leave her alone for now.

395
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:12,000
I don't understand.

396
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:15,080
Even now,
why can't she move on from Mr. Yai?

397
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:19,040
Seriously, do you really know
anything about love?

398
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:06,920
Here they come.

399
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:14,080
Why do we even have to line up
and welcome them? It's so grand.

400
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,840
- Should I ask Madam?
- No.

401
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,720
You're finally home.

402
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:31,680
What about Nee?

403
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:33,840
You didn't call her?

404
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:35,400
I told you to bring your sister back too.

405
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:38,240
I texted her, but she didn't reply.

406
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:41,080
She's probably drunk somewhere.

407
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,040
I'm going inside now.

408
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:46,120
Why are you people
just standing here? It's so hot.

409
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:49,880
Hey, why is no one holding
an umbrella for Ms. On?

410
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:53,640
You still haven't gone to prepare
warm water for Miss On's shower yet?

411
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,640
What are you spacing out for?

412
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:07,320
Is Aunt Un really dead?

413
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:11,360
Yes. Yai killed her.

414
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:20,960
Pin, go eat something.

415
00:42:21,040 --> 00:42:22,720
I'll take over here.

416
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:24,760
I'm not hungry.

417
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:27,560
I want to stay with Mom.

418
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:32,360
Pin.

419
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:38,440
I'm so sorry for your loss.

420
00:42:41,200 --> 00:42:43,440
Her life shouldn't have been cut so short.

421
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:46,080
We were shocked when we heard the news.

422
00:42:46,160 --> 00:42:47,600
Sorry for your loss, Pin.

423
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:50,080
Thank you so much, everyone.

424
00:42:58,800 --> 00:42:59,680
Where's Dad?

425
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:07,640
Uncle Win has been missing since
the day Madam Krongsuk took over the farm.

426
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:09,760
What did you say?

427
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:15,400
Un.

428
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,720
My dear Un…

429
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:29,000
How could you be so cruel
as to leave me like this?

430
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:34,880
Without you, how can I continue to live?

431
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,400
Who would love me like you do?

432
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:40,400
No one…

433
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:43,240
No one else would.

434
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:54,200
Thank you, Madam.

435
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:58,520
Pin.

436
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:09,840
Pin. I'm sorry.

437
00:44:11,560 --> 00:44:15,840
Yai wanted revenge against me,
but he took it out on Un.

438
00:44:17,560 --> 00:44:19,640
Un died because of me…

439
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:23,880
So dramatic.

440
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,480
She puts soap opera actors to shame.

441
00:44:31,720 --> 00:44:34,040
I caught you in the act,
you shameless bitch.

442
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:35,960
Even with your mom's corpse
lying in that coffin,

443
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:38,280
you still couldn't resist
messing around with someone's man.

444
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:41,720
- On?
- You killed Aunt Un, Uncle Paisal,

445
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,240
and Dad too!

446
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:45,680
Help!

447
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:48,280
<i>Find the right opportunity to silence her.</i>

448
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:49,480
Hey.

449
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:55,120
You're planning to kill Nee,
so how are we supposed to stay together?!

450
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:56,280
Hey.

451
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:38,400
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
